article.description: Marcus Keene scored 31 points, Braylon Rayson added 19 and Cecil Williams 13 as Central Michigan pulled away from Green Bay for an 89-77 win on Saturday.
article.headline: Keene pours in 31 in C. Michigan's 89-77 win over Green Bay
article.linkText: Keene pours in 31 in C. Michigan's 89-77 win over Green Bay
article.story: GREEN BAY, Wis. -- Marcus Keene scored 31 points, Braylon Rayson added 19 and Cecil Williams 13 as Central Michigan pulled away from Green Bay for an 89-77 win on Saturday. Turner Botz's 3 put Green Bay up 53-46 after halftime before Central Michigan (5-2) went on a 14-4 run. Williams's dunk with 10:51 to play put the Chippewas up 60-57. Green Bay got a 3 from Trevor Anderson to knot the score at 69 but Keene responded with an immediate 3 with 6:55 to go. Josh Kozinski added a 3 as did David DiLeo to give Central Michigan a six-point lead almost three minutes later. Central Michigan then outscored Green Bay (3-3) 11-3 the rest of the way. The Chippewas shot 14 for 36 (38.9 percent) from 3 compared to 6 for 26 (23.1) by the Phoenix. Charles Cooper led Green Bay with 20 points and seven rebounds.
